# Frontend Architecture

## Entry point
`main.tsx` wraps `<App>` in `<IslandSceneShell>` (scene backdrop + palms + day/night vars) inside `React.StrictMode`. The scene is always visible — including behind the login screen.

## Auth & routing
- `App.tsx` owns all state, all `apiFetch` calls, and all page routing.
- `isAuthenticated` starts `null` → `LoginScreen` until resolved.
- `page: PageId` is a string union, toggled by `setPage` passed as `onNavigate`.
- `isAdmin = profileData?.roleNames.includes("Parent")`.
- Pages never call `apiFetch` directly — they receive data + callbacks as props.

## Pages (apps/web/src/pages/)
| Page | Real data | Still mock |
|------|-----------|------------|
| `Home` | Featured game, friends online, activity feed (capped at 5, "View full feed" → Community), drift log | Bot/ritual CTAs |
| `Games` | Game nights + RSVP, session composer recs, Steam news, crew wishlist | Stream drawer (STREAMS_MOCK), mode chips (Tonight/Weekend/etc.) are local state only |
| `Library` | Full crew library + owner avatars + MINE badge | DETAILS button is non-functional |
| `Community` | Activity timeline | Crew carousel, clips, forums, clubs, events, leaderboards are hardcoded mock |
| `Admin` | News cards CRUD, server settings, recommendation tester | Data Sync, Members, Game Nights mod, Forums, Tournaments, Library subpages are stub UIs |
| `Profile` | MeProfile, owned games display + exclusion toggles | Excluded game IDs are client-only (not sent to API) |
| `Achievements` | — | Entire page is placeholder |

## Components (apps/web/src/components/)
- `Topbar` — `position: fixed` glass header (62px spacer div in App.tsx); global search is local state only (not wired to API)
- `UserMenu` — day/night toggle via `useDayNight`, Steam panel, profile/admin links, logout
- `SteamOnboarding` — post-login modal; skip state persisted per user in `localStorage`
- `steam.tsx` — Steam brand components + `steamSignInUrl()` pointing to `/steam/openid/start`

## Background sync intervals (App.tsx)
- Featured/activity/news: every 5 min
- Guild member sync: every 1 min
- Game nights list: every 20s (on Games page)
- Selected night refresh: every 15s
- Steam sync: every 10 min (when linked)

## Key types (apps/web/src/types.ts)
`PageId`, `MeProfile`, `GuildMember`, `GameNight`, `GameNightAttendee`, `CrewOwnedGame`, `CrewWishlistGame`, `FeaturedRecommendation`, `GameNewsItem`, `ActivityEvent`, `NewsCard`, `ServerSetting`
